---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import GtmNoscript from '../components/GtmNoscript.astro';

const title = 'Privacy';
const description =
	'How hungovercoders handles analytics and marketing data, and what your cookie consent choices control';
---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={title} description={description} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<GtmNoscript />
		<Header />
		<main id="main-content" class="prose">
			<h1>Privacy</h1>

			<p>
				This page explains what data hungovercoders collects, why, and how you stay in control of it.
				Nothing analytics- or marketing-related runs until you choose — see <a href="#your-choices"
					>your choices</a
				> below.
			</p>

			<h2>Who we are</h2>
			<p>
				hungovercoders (dataGriff) is the data controller for this site, <code
					>hungovercoders.com</code
				>. If you have a question about your data, get in touch via the <a href="/about">About</a> page
				or the GitHub links in the footer.
			</p>

			<h2>Cookies and data we use</h2>
			<p>
				<strong>Analytics (only with your consent).</strong> If you consent to analytics we use Google
				Analytics 4 (measurement ID <code>G-D95TZQ8QFT</code>), loaded through Google Tag Manager. It
				sets <code>_ga</code> and <code>_ga_*</code> cookies and collects the <a
					href="https://support.google.com/analytics/answer/11593727?hl=en"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer">default data for Google Analytics 4</a
				> — approximate location, device and browser, and the pages you visit — for website performance
				monitoring. It does not include personally identifiable data. GA4 retains this data for the
				property's configured retention period, after which it is deleted.
			</p>
			<p>
				<strong>Consent (strictly necessary).</strong> A <code>consent</code> cookie remembers your cookie
				choices for 12 months so you aren't asked on every visit. It carries no analytics or marketing
				data and is set regardless of your choices, because it only stores those choices.
			</p>
			<p>
				<strong>Marketing.</strong> No user data is collected for marketing purposes, regardless of consent.
			</p>

			<h2>Legal basis</h2>
			<p>
				Analytics relies on your <strong>consent</strong> under UK GDPR and PECR. Until you accept,
				analytics does not load and no analytics cookies are set. The strictly necessary consent cookie
				relies on our legitimate interest in remembering your preference.
			</p>

			<h2>Sharing and international transfers</h2>
			<p>
				Google acts as our processor for Google Analytics. Your analytics data may be processed outside
				the UK and EEA; Google provides safeguards for those transfers, described in the <a
					href="https://policies.google.com/privacy"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Privacy Policy</a
				>. We do not sell your data or share it with anyone else.
			</p>

			<h2 id="your-choices">Your choices</h2>
			<p>
				You can change or withdraw your consent at any time — it's as easy as giving it. Use the button
				below (also in the footer of every page) to reopen the cookie preferences, or clear this site's
				cookies in your browser settings.
			</p>
			<p>
				<button type="button" class="cookie-prefs">Manage cookie preferences</button>
			</p>
			<p>
				Under UK GDPR you also have the right to access or request erasure of your personal data — get in
				touch via the <a href="/about">About</a> page.
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	.prose {
		max-width: 720px;
		margin: 3rem auto;
		padding: 0 1rem;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
	}
	.prose h1 {
		margin-bottom: 0.5em;
	}
	.prose h2 {
		margin-top: 1.5em;
	}
	.cookie-prefs {
		background: none;
		border: 0;
		padding: 0;
		font: inherit;
		color: var(--accent);
		text-decoration: underline;
		cursor: pointer;
	}
</style>
